          between 2000q1 to 2017q4. Data for the study were sourced from Central Bank of Nigeria
          Statistical Bulletin, 2017, Edition and National Bureau of Statistics. The study employed
          Threshold Autoregressive model as estimation technique. Finding from the study showed that
          threshold level of inflation above which inflation becomes inimical for the stock market returns
          in Nigeria was 12.3%. The estimation results further showed that there was negative
          relationship between inflation and stock market returns in Nigeria. This is because, the
          estimated inflation was above the suggested threshold level of inflation, which was 12.3% in
          Nigeria. Based on this finding, the study therefore, concludes that inflation impacts stock
          market returns in Nigeria negatively during the study period. The study recommends that
          monetary authority can use inflation target to provide stable and friendly environments for the
          growth of stock market in Nigeria.</article>
