          level while others variables were stationary at first difference. Johansen co-integration test
          result showed 2 co-integrating equations at the 0.05 level. The study findings revealed that
          electricity consumption has no significant impact on consumersâ€™ welfare in Nigeria. Also, the
          study revealed that consumer price index, poverty rate and unemployment have an inverse
          relationship with real gross domestic product in Nigeria. Therefore, the study recommended
          cogent approach towards reforming electricity supply to meet demand of the populace and to
          improve the consumersâ€™ welfare.</article>
